main event: An observer reported a UFO sighting in Miamisburg, Ohio on February 7, 1969, but failed to submit any photographs or detailed information for evaluation as of April 15, 1969.
interesting points: The observer reported seeing a UFO but did not submit photographs or complete the required forms,The Air Force requested that the observer provide more information and original negatives for analysis,The report concluded there was insufficient data for a meaningful evaluation, The document included various illustrations and a diagram related to the sighting but no actual photos were provided, The contact mentioned in the report, Lt. O. D. Anderson, indicated a desire to discuss the sighting further.
witness description: Observer who reported the sighting but did not provide detailed follow-up
